---
import '../../styles/sections/about.css';
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SectionHeader from '../../components/ui/SectionHeader.astro';
import Divider from '../../components/global/Divider.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Qi-Lab" description="Learn about Qi-Lab's brand story, philosophy, and contact information.">
  <div class="about-page">
    <div class="container">

      <!-- Page Hero -->
      <section class="page-hero" data-reveal>
        <span class="page-label">// ABOUT</span>
        <h1 class="page-title">About Qi-Lab</h1>
        <p class="page-subtitle">
          A personal brand focused on technology, design, and creativity
        </p>
      </section>

      <Divider />

      <!-- Brand Story -->
      <section class="about-section" data-reveal>
        <SectionHeader label="// STORY" title="Brand Story" />
        <div class="about-prose">
          <p>
            QiLab is my digital archive. The name "Qi" represents the persistent pursuit of systematic organization, 
            while "Yan" represents the rigorous exploration of technical depth. In the age of information overload, 
            I believe that structured knowledge is true power. Here, we don't sell anxiety or quick fixes, 
            only record real pitfalls and verified experiences.
          </p>
          <p>
            I focus on four intersecting areas: knowledge management, project management, IT/AI skills, and cutting-edge trends. 
            In daily practice, I use Obsidian to build knowledge graphs based on Bloom's six-layer cognitive model, 
            Markdown + Git to maintain a single source of truth documentation system, 
            and AI Agents (Superpowers + OpenClaw) to drive development and content production pipelines. 
            Every share is verified through actual use.
          </p>
          <p>
            As a senior information systems project management professional with 7 hard certifications including PMP, ITIL, and CCNP, 
            I deeply understand that "hoarding is not management, choosing to slow down is itself a form of resistance". 
            From the zero-new-feature refactoring of SystemPM, to the data pipeline reconstruction of StockAAssist, 
            to the ground-up construction of the QiLab knowledge base — each time is a practice of the engineering philosophy 
            of "systematic root cause rather than patching".
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <Divider />

      <!-- Philosophy -->
      <section class="about-section" data-reveal>
        <SectionHeader label="// PHILOSOPHY" title="Design Philosophy" />
        <div class="philosophy-grid">
          <div class="philosophy-card">
            <span class="philosophy-number">01</span>
            <h3 class="philosophy-title">Qi-Lab</h3>
            <p class="philosophy-desc">
              A visual philosophy designed for workers at their desks late at night. The oat gray background is like warm paper, 
              the emerald cursor flickers with rational light, and the amber gold desk lamp casts warm companionship. 
              Core metaphor: a study with a desk lamp on late at night. Pursue a clear, comfortable, breathable visual environment, 
              using low cognitive load design to offset the mental consumption of high-density information.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="philosophy-card">
            <span class="philosophy-number">02</span>
            <h3 class="philosophy-title">Engineering Aesthetics & Functional Isolation</h3>
            <p class="philosophy-desc">
              Code is not just a functional implementation, but also a systematic expression. CSS design tokens build a complete Qi-Lab visual system, 
              fonts strictly divided into three categories (serif for titles → scholarly feel, sans-serif for body → clarity, monospace for code → geeky feel), 
              Bento Grid with 24px spacing ensures spatial order. Readability, maintainability, and aesthetics are all essential.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="philosophy-card">
            <span class="philosophy-number">03</span>
            <h3 class="philosophy-title">Long-termism & Real Verification</h3>
            <p class="philosophy-desc">
              Rather than selling anxiety, we'd rather walk the death valley from 0 to 100 followers. Every tool recommendation is verified through actual use, 
              every technical viewpoint comes from real project pitfalls. Adhere to human ontological value — in an era where AI can generate everything, 
              human thinking, judgment, and creativity are even more precious. Every share is a proof of real existence.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <Divider />

      <!-- Contact CTA -->
      <section class="about-section" data-reveal>
        <SectionHeader label="// CONTACT" title="Get in Touch" />
        <div class="contact-cta">
          <p class="cta-text">
            Whether it's knowledge management exchange, AI workflow discussion, or project cooperation, 
            feel free to contact us anytime.
          </p>
          <div class="cta-links">
            <a href="mailto:matthewhemhgz@gmail.com" class="cta-link">
              <span class="cta-label">Email</span>
              <span class="cta-value">matthewhemhgz@gmail.com</span>
            </a>
            <div class="cta-link">
              <span class="cta-label">WeChat</span>
              <span class="cta-value">祈研所或 QiLab</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <a href="/en#contact" class="cta-btn">View Full Contact Information</a>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>